<TITLE> 'Extortion' behind Badda shootings </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 12 (bdnews24.com)  Criminals shot and wounded two men in Badda on Sunday morning. Police said the men were shot when criminals demanded protection money from Ashkar Ali, 35, and Kamal Hossain, 25. Both men were admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital for treatment. Badda thana sub-inspector Abdur Razzak said a group of ten to twelve gang members were active on the eve of the opening of Hossain Market. Officials said local gang members were demanding Tk 5 lakh per shop. Police suspected that the group used the shooting to intimidate the businessmen in the market. An eyewitness, Baharuddin, an assistant to the injured Kamal at the Salam Engineering Workshop, said 15 to 20 gang members were randomly firing in front of the market Sunday morning. Baharuddin said the local gang leader, Mia Bhai, was demanding extortion money from every shop in the newly established market. Preferring anonymity, one businessman said, "After reaching me in the Dhaka Medical College Hospital, Mia Bhai asked me over the phone, 'Why did you not hand over the money? Let's see what happens to you?'" Businessmen in the market are frightened, according to witnesses. bdn
